com.sk89q.intake.parametric.handler

Interface InvokeHandler

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    LegacyCommandsHandler

    public interface InvokeHandler
    Called before and after a command is invoked for commands executed by a command created with ParametricBuilder.

    Invocation handlers are created by InvokeListeners. Multiple listeners and handlers can be registered, and all be run. However, if one handler throws an exception, future handlers will not execute and the command will not execute (if thrown in preInvoke(Object, Method, ParameterData[], Object[], CommandContext, CommandLocals)).

    See Also:
    the factory
